2. Multi-Node Global Storage Setup
Because your cluster schedules work across multiple machines (like k8s-worker-1), your media assets must live in a standardized global directory on the worker node where your pods run:

Bash
# 1. On your Control Plane VM, copy images to a clean cluster directory
sudo mkdir -p /data/photos
sudo cp ~/kube/project1/photos/* /data/photos/
sudo chmod -R 755 /data/photos

# 2. Sync the images over the network to your active Worker Node drive
sudo scp -r /data/photos/* system@k8s-worker-1:/data/photos/

# 3. SSH into k8s-worker-1 to ensure the background Kubelet account can read them
ssh system@k8s-worker-1
sudo chmod -R 755 /data/photos
exit
3. The Unified Production Manifest (test-dir/nginx-project.yaml)
This production file structures your static storage components, builds your responsive CSS gallery layout via a ConfigMap, mounts the directories to your Nginx containers, and isolates access within a secure ClusterIP network:

YAML
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: photo-storage-pv
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: 5Gi
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
  hostPath:
    path: /data/photos
    type: Directory
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: photo-storage-pvc
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  storageClassName: ""
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 5Gi
  volumeName: photo-storage-pv
---
