apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: photography-nginx
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: photography-web
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: photography-web
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:alpine
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        volumeMounts:
        - name: html-volume
          mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
          subPath: index.html
        - name: images-volume
          mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html/images
      volumes:
      - name: html-volume
        configMap:
          name: nginx-html-config
      - name: images-volume
        persistentVolumeClaim:
          claimName: photo-storage-pvc
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: photography-service
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80
    protocol: TCP
  selector:
    app: photography-web
4. Operational & Deployment Execution
Execute these commands step-by-step to push changes to your cluster and sync your remote Git repository:

Cluster Application & Rolling Cache Invalidation
Bash
# 1. Clean up old immutable structures
kubectl delete pv photo-storage-pv

# 2. Deploy your clean sheet manifest
kubectl apply -f test-dir/nginx-project.yaml

# 3. Force Nginx to evict stale runtime code and fetch your new 12-image grid configuration
kubectl rollout restart deployment/photography-nginx

# 4. Check that your pods go completely green
kubectl get pods -w
Git Repository Synchronization (Resolving Out-of-Sync Rejections)
Bash
# 1. Pull down changes sitting on GitHub and merge them with your local commits
git pull origin main --no-rebase
# Note: If a text prompt opens, save and close to complete the merge.

# 2. Securely push your local 14 file modifications to your github remote repository
git push origin main
Launching the Secure Proxy Tunnel to Windows Chrome
To cross your Host-Only network adapter boundaries safely without using a public Ingress controller, establish this proxy channel:

Bash
kubectl port-forward svc/photography-service --address 0.0.0.0 8080:80
Open Google Chrome on Windows and go to your custom local domain: [http://my-nginx.local:8080](http://my-nginx.local:8080) (or [http://192.168.56.101:8080](http://192.168.56.101:8080)). Press Ctrl + F5 once it loads to flush any lingering browser cache!
